<p />
<blockquote style="background-color:#f0f0f0">
<strong>Example: WebFormTemplate from the TWiki.Know web</strong>
</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#D0FFD0" colspan ="2"><b> Changed: </b></td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#FF4040" valign="top" width="1%">&lt;<br />&lt;</td><td><p />
<h3><a name ="Defining_a_Form_in_Multiple_Topi"> </a> Defining a Form in Multiple Topics </h3>
</td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#40FF40" valign="top" width="1%">&gt;<br />&gt;</td><td>
<p />
<h3><a name ="Defining_a_Form_with_Multiple_To"> </a> Defining a Form with Multiple Topics </h3>
</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#D0FFD0" colspan ="2"><b> Changed: </b></td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#FF4040" valign="top" width="1%">&lt;<br />&lt;</td><td><p />
<ul >
<li> A Form Template topic defines the form.
</li>
<li> Values of fields that have more then one value - radio, select, checkbox - can be defined by field value Template topics.
</li>
</ul>
</td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#40FF40" valign="top" width="1%">&gt;<br />&gt;</td><td>
<p />
<ul >
<li> A Form Template topic defines the Form.
</li>
<li> Fields that have more then one value - radio, select, checkbox - can be defined in individual field value topics.
</li>
</ul>
</td></tr>
